          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2021-08-17 06:36:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified+1\n\nPassed enforced test review-ldiskfs-dne on CentOS 8.3/x86_64 uploaded by Onyx Autotest from onyx-25vm1: https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/67167de4-16a8-4547-8e71-4f60281759e3 ran 5 tests.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c523e62b1f1348899aead45090fbd1ec9c2abe9f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 148,
        "name": "Chris Horn",
        "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
        "username": "hornc"
      },
      "date": "2021-08-17 16:12:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nI believe this change reintroduces the breakage that was fixed by LU-13785 unless you explicitly set the hop count to 1.\n\n> Changes introduced by LU-13785 interpret default hops to be equivalent to hop=1\n\nThis change was intentional. Historically, the default hop count, if one was not specified, was \"1\". LNET_UNDEFINED_HOPS was introduced in\n\n  LU-6851 lnet: Ignore hops if not explicitly set\n\n\nThat commit states:\n\n> To keep existing behavior both lnet_compare_routes() and LNetDist() will treat undefined hop count as hop count 1.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b30b64a1c799eee2816fad07eb63482e4bb2bd82",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 148,
        "name": "Chris Horn",
        "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
        "username": "hornc"
      },
      "date": "2021-08-25 20:46:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nAfter discussing this with Serguei, and re-reading some of those historical tickets, I realized that I was wrong w.r.t. my assumptions about required hop-counts as they relate to the ARF feature. This change aligns us with how this feature worked historically, so I approve.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "bbf8bc3bc3fdb5b34a95fa64c3cf0a90a02d2eda",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2021-08-25 23:54:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
